│     // Operand 0 may be transiently undef if its defining cleanuppad was │
│ deleted.                                                                 │
│     // Use the raw operand to preserve this state without asserting.     │
│     Value *Pad = CRI->getOperand(0);                                     │
│     NewTI = CleanupReturnInst::Create(Pad, nullptr, CRI->getIterator()); │
│     UnwindDest = CRI->getUnwindDest();                                   │
│   } else if (...)                                                        │
│                                                                          │
│ Rationale:                                                               │
│ - CleanupReturnInst::Create accepts a Value* for the pad and asserts it  │
│ is non-null, but does not require it to be a CleanupPadInst at           │
│ construction time. Using the raw operand preserves undef values and      │
│ avoids the cast in getCleanupPad(). Subsequent code which might query    │
│ getCleanupPad() already contains guards (e.g., simplifyCleanupReturn) to │
│ skip processing when operand 0 is undef.                                 │
│ - This keeps removeUnwindEdge robust in the presence of transient undef  │
│ EH pad operands created by prior unreachable/dead block deletion.        │
│                                                                          │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                           │
│ The crash is caused by removeUnwindEdge assuming that the cleanuppad     │
│ operand of a cleanupret is always a CleanupPadInst and calling           │
│ getCleanupPad(), while simplifycfg can create a transient state where    │
│ that operand becomes undef after deleting the defining EH pad block.     │
│ Updating removeUnwindEdge to construct the replacement cleanupret using  │
│ CRI->getOperand(0) instead of CRI->getCleanupPad() avoids the invalid    │
│ cast and aligns with existing simplifycfg logic that tolerates undef EH  │
│ pad operands. This fixes the assertion and allows simplifycfg to proceed │
│ safely.                                                                  │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                          │
